  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Legal definitions typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into legitimate economy\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but most include:\n- Intentionally disguising criminal proceeds\n- Transferring or converting property knowing it represents criminal activity\n- Concealing or disguising the true nature of criminal funds\n\nPrecise details depend on individual country's financial crime statutes.",
